body:
Hello everybody,

maybe you are here because you get know my javascript library **Class**.

I want to show you some examples what the library can do:

**1)** Define a class. 
For example you could have a Pizza.js file. 

```javascript
// Pizza.js
Class.define('Pizza', {
   name : 'Pizza',
   price : 10
});

// In another *.js file you could create an instance of Pizza.
var pizza = Class.create('Pizza');
```

**2)** Doing inheritance:
```javascript
// SalamiPizza.js
Class.define('SalamiPizza', {
   extend : 'Pizza', // key "extend" tells you the super class.
   name : 'SalamiPizza'
});
```

**3)** Work with constructor.
```javascript
// SalamiPizza.js
Class.define('SalamiPizza', {
   extend : 'Pizza', // key "extend" tells you the super class.
   init : function() { // init() will be automatically called 
                       // by creating a SalamiPizza.
      this.name = 'SalamiPizza';
   }
});
```

**4)** In addition the constructor can take as many parameters you want.
```javascript
// SalamiPizza.js
Class.define('SalamiPizza', {
   extend : 'Pizza', // key "extend" tells you the super class.
   init : function(name, price) { // init() will be automatically 
                                  // called by creating a SalamiPizza.
      this.name = name;   
      this.price = price;
   }
});

// Just add parameters for the constructor after class name:
var salamiPizza = Class.create('SalamiPizza', 'SalamiPizza', 20);
```

**4)** Static property and methods
You can give your classes static methods and properties, too.
Example:
```javascript
Class.define('Example', {
   staticProperty : {
      type : 'static',
      value : 'test'
   },
   staticMethod : {
      type : 'static',
      value : function() {
         return 'bla';	
      }
   }
});
```

Well, that`s it. 
If you have any suggestions I would be happy for feedback.

Have a nice day and lots of fun with class.js. :-)
